{
  "texts": [
    "A theoretical analysis of the indexing and search algorithms is an open research question (no existing graph-based vector search method provides this analysis), and is out-of-scope.",
    "The extension to the out-of-core scenario and the theoretical analysis are both part of our future work.",
    "PreliminariesThe 𝑛𝑔-approximate vector search problem is typically modeled as an 𝑛𝑔-approximate 𝑘-NN search problem in high-dimensional vector space.",
    "Data points are represented as 𝑑-dimensional vectors in 𝑅 𝑑, and the dissimilarity between the points is measured using the Euclidean distance dist.",
    "We consider a dataset collection 𝑆 = {𝑉 𝐶 1, 𝑉 𝐶 2,..., 𝑉 𝐶 𝑛 } of 𝑛 𝑑-dimensional points and a query vector 𝑉 𝑄."
  ]
}